so R-squerd = 0.7737 means our model can can explain 77% of variation in observed data valus . as we know f-statistic in here computed by F = [R² / (k-1)] / [ (1-R²) (n-k) ] that shows if this R2 -squered can mean that by adding these ten variable to model instead of zero variable (mean value) our model can explain this variation on observed data . F Statistic gives us a power to judge whether that relationship is statistically significant in other words it comments on whether or R² is significant or not. for F-stat = 495.4 and DF =10 we get too small p-value that we can reject that Additional variables do not provide value taken together.
